==Non-government right-to-repair organizations==
There is a growing list of non-governmental organizations that advocate for the right to repair from independent NGO advocacy groups to industry sponsored organizations that advocate for their industry members. These groups include:

;Canada
*[https://www.canrepair.ca Canrepair.ca] - website of the Canadian Repair Coalition (Canadian-based group of repair professionals, individuals, academics, industry associations and firms that support Right to Repair policies at all levels of government)
;EU
*[https://repair.eu Repair.eu] - website of the Right to Repair Europe Coalition, which represents over 170 organizations from 27 European countries. It includes environmental NGOs and repair actors such as community repair groups, social economy actors, spare parts distributors, self-repairers, repair and refurbishing businesses. 
;USA
*[https://www.repair.org Repair.org] - website of the Repair Association (US-based group of mostly smaller repair professionals and firms that support Right to Repair policies)
*[https://pirg.org/campaigns/right-to-repair/ Pirg.org/campaigns/right-to-repair] - website for the U.S. Public Interest Research Group's (PIRG's) right-to-repair campaign. US PIRG is a leading advocate for right-to-repair legislation at both the state and federal level. 
*[https://www.ifixit.com/Right-to-Repair iFixit.com] - website for iFixit's right-to-repair campaign page. iFixit is a leading source of online information regarding device repair and a leading advocate for right-to-repair laws.
*[https://fulu.org/ Fulu Foundation] - Created by [[Louis Rossmann]] and Eron Jokipii in 2023 to expose companies anti-[[ownership]] practices, educate the public, unite those in the repair industry, and lobby to reform anti repair legislation.
*[https://consumerrights.wiki/w/Main_Page Consumer Rights Wiki] - Website for people to document companies and products that violate the right to repair. Created by [[Louis Rossmann]] in 2024.

There are also innumerable [[Repair Café]]s that are run in communities around the world. Some are sponsored by municipalities and others are mainly unaffiliated.

